{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17646787","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17646787"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:35:48+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:35:48+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18205"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18205","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18205"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0,0.06,0.84,0.1]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10919"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73811"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10919","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10919"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18205"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59286"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4936"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"5294"},{"type":"tags","id":"5296"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25382"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25385"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73811","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/73811"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EDisease-modifying antirheumatic drugs (DMARDs) are used to treat autoimmune conditions such as rheumatoid arthritis. One of these drugs acts as a folic acid antagonist with cytotoxic and immunosuppressant activity by inhibiting dihydrofolate reductase.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following disease-modifying antirheumatic drugs acts by inhibiting dihydrofolate reductase?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Penicillamine","Leflunomide","Hydroxychloroquine","Methotrexate","Sulfasalazine"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMethotrexate\u003C/strong\u003E is the disease-modifying antirheumatic drug that acts by inhibiting dihydrofolate reductase. This inhibition leads to reduced folic acid synthesis, which is necessary for DNA synthesis and cell replication, resulting in its cytotoxic and immunosuppressant effects.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELeflunomide\u003C/strong\u003E - Inhibits pyrimidine synthesis\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHydroxychloroquine\u003C/strong\u003E - Modulates immune system activity but does not inhibit dihydrofolate reductase\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESulfasalazine\u003C/strong\u003E - Has anti-inflammatory properties but does not act on dihydrofolate reductase\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPenicillamine\u003C/strong\u003E - Acts as a chelating agent and does not inhibit dihydrofolate reductase\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Methotrexate is a disease-modifying antirheumatic drug that acts as a folic acid antagonist.","Methotrexate inhibits dihydrofolate reductase, leading to cytotoxic and immunosuppressant effects.","Methotrexate is commonly used in the treatment of rheumatoid arthritis and other autoimmune conditions."],"references":["Tian H, Cronstein BN. Understanding the mechanisms of action of methotrexate: implications for the treatment of rheumatoid arthritis. Bull NYU Hosp Jt Dis. 2007;65(3):168-73. PMID: 17922664.","Waller, D. G., \u0026 Hitchings, A. W. (2021). Medical Pharmacology and Therapeutics E-Book: Medical Pharmacology and Therapeutics E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Tashjian, A. H., \u0026 Armstrong, E. J. (2011). Principles of pharmacology: the pathophysiologic basis of drug therapy. Lippincott Williams \u0026 Wilkins","Queremel Milani DA, Davis DD. Pain Management Medications. 2023 Jul 3. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32809527","Carter GT, Duong V, Ho S, Ngo KC, Greer CL, Weeks DL. Side effects of commonly prescribed analgesic medications. Phys Med Rehabil Clin N Am. 2014 May;25(2):457-70. doi: 10.1016/j.pmr.2014.01.007. PMID: 24787343"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59286"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18205"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59286","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/59286"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-24T04:31:45+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-24T04:32:29+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10919"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73811"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tag